## Requirements

```
torch>=2.1
transformers>=4.35
peft>=0.7  (for LoRA)
pandas
numpy
scipy
scikit-learn
mmseqs2  (for antigen clustering, system install)
wandb  (optional, for experiment tracking)
biopython
```

> [!NOTE]
> **GPU**: NVIDIA H100 (80GB). This comfortably fits ESM-2 650M with LoRA, batch size 32, and bf16 precision. No model size compromises needed.

---

## Confirmed Decisions

- ✅ **Backbone**: ESM-2 650M for all sequences
- ✅ **Affinity types**: 6 separate multi-task heads, no harmonization
- ✅ **GPU**: H100 (80GB) — bf16, batch size 32
- ✅ **Tracking**: Weights & Biases (wandb)
- ✅ **Data**: Only `asd_regression_ready_hla.csv` (164K rows)
- ✅ **Light chain bias mitigation**: Light chain masking (30% of training steps) + balanced sampling

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Unit tests for data loading, splitting, and model forward pass
- Integration test: train for 2 epochs on 1% sample, verify loss decreases
- LOAFO cross-validation with metrics logged per fold

### Manual Verification
- Review per-antigen scatter plots (predicted vs. actual affinity)
- Check that LOAFO performance on held-out families is non-random (Pearson > 0.3)
- Verify gradient reversal is reducing antigen-family predictability from shared features
